<br>
<br>
A great lunch to prepare in advance and take to work with you. This makes four portions, and will keep for a few days in the refrigerator.</a>.<br>
<br>
<b>Ingredients</b>
<br><div class="mobileAdPlacement"></div>
<ul><li> 1 cup quinoa </li><li> 1/3 cup freshly squeezed lemon juice </li><li>1/3 cup good-quality olive oil</li><li>¾ tsp. kosher salt</li><li>1 cup cherry tomatoes, halved</li><li>¼ cup minced green onion</li><li>½ English cucumber, diced</li><li>¼ cup diced red onion</li><li>½ cup chopped fresh basil</li><li>½ cup chopped flat-leaf parsley</li><li>3 Tbsp. chopped dill</li><li>2 cups baby kale</li><li>¼ lb. bocconcini cheese</li></ul><br>
<b>Preparation time:</b> 20 minutes<br>
<br>
<b>Cook time:</b> 20 minutes<br><br>
<b>Rest time:</b> 1 hour<br><br>
<b>Steps:</b>
<br><div class="teadsAdPlacement"></div>
1. Cook the quinoa according to the package directions. Transfer to a large bowl. <br>
2. Whisk together the lemon juice, olive oil, and salt in a small bowl and pour over the warm quinoa. Toss well to combine.<br>
3. Add the tomatoes, green onions, cucumber, red onion, basil and parsley and stir well. Taste and adjust seasonings if necessary. Add the baby kale and toss to combine. Tear the bocconcini into pieces and scatter it over the salad.<br>
4. Let the salad sit at room temperature for 1 hour in order for the flavours to incorporate before serving. Alternatively, feel free to refrigerate the salad overnight. If refrigerated, bring back to room temperature and check the seasonings before serving.
